{
  "answer": "In Mirza Ghalib's *Diwan-e-Ghalib*, the heart (*dil*) is a recurrent motif, often embodying profound emotional vulnerability. One famous couplet portrays it as exquisitely precious—tender and alive, inherently susceptible to pain in a way inert stone or brick could never be:\n\n> It is a heart, not stone and brick, that fills with pain;  \n> We'll weep a thousand times—why should a soul be slain?[^1]\n\nHere, the heart's capacity for deep suffering underscores its value as the seat of authentic human experience, fragile yet essential.[^2]\n\nBy contrast, another couplet depicts the heart as utterly disposable amid existential helplessness, reduced to a negligible drop of blood that's already lost and inconsequential:\n\n> On helplessness's board, one heart was my domain,  \n> A single drop of blood, and that too lost in rain.[^3]\n\nIn this image, the heart is not a cherished core but a fleeting, expendable entity on the \"board\" (*bisaat*) of powerlessness, bowed low and leaking away without purpose or notice.[^4]\n\nThese couplets exemplify Ghalib's paradoxical treatment of *dil*: a vital, irreplaceable organ in moments of raw emotion, yet dismissible in the face of fate's indifference.\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/33-dil-hi-to-hai-na-sang-o-khisht-dard-se-bhar-na-aay/translation/#p-d9d50d).\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, chapter 33 (*Dil hi to hai na sang-o-khisht, dard se bhar na aaye kyun-*), [translation](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/33-dil-hi-to-hai-na-sang-o-khisht-dard-se-bhar-na-aay/translation/).\n\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/20-bisaat-e-ijz-mein-tha-ek-dil-yak-qatra-e-khoon-woh/translation/#p-46c8d1).\n\n[^4]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, chapter 20 (*Bisaat-e-ijz mein tha ek dil, yak qatra-e-khoon, woh bhi*), [translation](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/20-bisaat-e-ijz-mein-tha-ek-dil-yak-qatra-e-khoon-woh/translation/).",
